We have recommended that the Management:

a) Advice the Rural Improvement Club (RIC) Lal-lo Chapter, to furnish this Audit Team, thru the Accounting Office, its eligibility documents in order to qualify as a beneficiary of the projects of the LGU in accordance Section 4.4 of COA Circular No. 2007-001 dated October 25, 2007;

b) Stop the payment of ordinary expenses of NGOs/POs and extend financial assistance to support qualified projects bound by the terms and stipulations of a Memorandum of Agreement (MOA) of the LGU with the RIC and include an income sharing clause in the MOA pursuant to Section 4.5.8 of the Circular;

c) Assign personnel to monitor and evaluate the activities of the accredited NGO’s/ PO’s as set out under Item h of Paragraph 45.3 of the same regulation; and

d) Comply with all the provisions of the Circular to control and monitor the grant of government funds to accredited NGOs/POs.

a)	Direct all concerned departments who are receiving goods in-kind from National Government Agencies or from any source, to inform and coordinate with the General Services Office (GSO), for the inspection and receipt of such goods, before issuance to the concerned end users or recipients; 

b)	Advise the GSO to prepare the reports as mandated under COA Circular No. 2014-002 dated April 15, 2014 to attain transparency in the receipt, distribution and issuance of all in-kind donations and ensure that the donations have reached the intended recipients, then furnish the accounting office the necessary records on the receipt and issuance for proper recording in the books of accounts; and

c)	Instruct the accounting office to make necessary adjustment to recognize the unrecorded transactions and effect prompt recognition in the books of accounts all forthcoming in-kind donations pursuant to Sections 187 and 188 of the GAM for LGUs prescribed under COA Circular 2020-004 dated January 31, 2020.

